-- Button Wins Season-Opening Australian Formula One Grand Prix
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-03-18T07:40:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/button-wins-season-opening-australian-formula-one-grand-prix.html
Jenson Button  of McLaren won the
Australian Grand Prix, the opening race of the 2012 Formula One
world championship  Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel, who’s bidding to win his third
straight world title, was second in the 58-lap race at
Melbourne’s Albert Park circuit.  Lewis Hamilton  in the other
McLaren was third ahead of Red Bull’s Mark Webber.  Button’s third victory in Melbourne lifted him within one
of Michael Schumacher’s record four victories.  The next event in the 20-race calendar is scheduled March
25 in Malaysia.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  